*If you want to create more appealing faces for humans I suggest using "(comedone, skin cancer, psoriasis, eczema, herpes)” it in your negative prompt.

  If you are creating creatures or odd things, my suggestion is to leaving off   “(comedone, skin cancer, psoriasis, eczema, herpes)”. (NOTE:This is not my negative, i found it on someone else’s post.) The ai likes to NOT give you goosebump or creepy art if you use that in the negative prompt while focusing on that type of image.

Another trick I have learned is trying things like “(LESS_THAN_GREG_RUTKOWSKI)” in the negative prompt, it makes a DRAMATIC change in your image… like mind blowing sometimes. (NOTE: THIS part is my idea, one day i just said fuck it, im putting alot of this postive stuff in the negative prompt but wording it “LESS_THAN” format and BOOM!!! ) I look forward to seeing what you try in your negative prompt. If you get a pokemon that is deformed for example , try (DEFORMED_POKEMON:1.3) in your negative prompt that worked for me to remove extra pikachu ears and arms. This is experimental stuff so please don’t hold me to it, just remember to have fun.

BBMIX-JOY

It was a merged model for me to enjoy painting alone, but I have many friends asking what model it is, so I'm revealing it. The face is chic, but the body is a model whose weight is adjusted so that it is output in a healthy way.

Her round appearance, big waist and thick thighs are attractive.

referral prompt

  • from above, from below

  • shiny skin, nice leg line: 1.3, thick thighs, thin waist,

negative

  • {1$$EasyNegative|verybadimagenegative_v1.3}

VAE

  • clearvae_main , clearvae_main2

  • vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned


We will continue to add sample images after finding good Loras so that we can copy and use EXIF in the sample post.

Precautions (Be sure to observe this)

  1. Models may not be traded or sold. Because this is free. .

  2. Models are not available for online paid services. (Free service available)

  3. In using the model, all responsibility lies with the user.

How to high quality

  1. You can output an image like the sample by using an extension to increase the quality. (All sample images were used with the extensions below)

  • 1. Hires.fix -> SwinIR_4x or R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B

  • 2. Dynamic Thresholding (CFG Scale Fix)

  • 3. Detection Detailer (must use)

  • 4. SD upscaler or https://oo.pe/https://www.upscayl.org/

1.Hires.fix ( built-in ) or

2. Dynamic Thresholding

https://github.com/mcmonkeyprojects/sd-dynamic-thresholding.git

3.Detection Detailer

https://github.com/Bing-su/dddetailer.git

Questions that do not use the above four cannot be answered. Please note that images printed without using the four extensions may not look good.

TIP

In order to keep token 75, do not insert resolution, detail, or quality tokens. Since extension add-ons such as DD or DT handle it anyway, there is no need to insert tokens like the ones below.

bad prompt (do not use)

official art, unity 8k wallpaper, ultra detailed, ultra high res, 8k uhd, film grain, delicate, RAW, light particles, detailed skin texture, detailed armor texture, detailed face, intricate details, ultra detailed

Reality Emphasis Prompt Excludes Detail Emphasis Prompt.

Modill

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

Declaration: I suggest illustrators and arts cannot be replaced by AI, although these models can accelerate design/drawing, the details, sprite-inside, visual-logics cannot be Datafication in Neural Networks.

-----------------------------——·--··c🫰c--··—--------------------------------

⚡️⚡️New Modill v2.0 released⚡️⚡️

The train dataset has 500 illustration, 3000 steps.

Train dataset:816*816

CFG scale:7-8

Sampling Steps:20-30

Suggested sampler: Euler, DPM2 a, DPM++ 2S a Karras

Trigger words: editorial illustration

Because the illustrated characters aren’t normal body structure, some multiples arms, legs often occur, pls add Hires.fix to adjust.

Next version will focus on 2.5d and 3d illustration.

 

All train data collection are human-manual, and training cloud environment costs me much. hope your donation to support my new model. https://ko-fi.com/cecily34

If you have any questions related to the model or its samples, how to get started or just want to share your creations, feel free to join my discord: https://discord.gg/GgZFF3qPEB

That is my pleasure.

🌸 Loves U.

🔥Modill🔥 (Modern-Illustration) is a trained checkpoint to make attractive and creative illustrations/painting. It can generate some flat illustrations for both business and creative-design. Trained by 289 brilliant illustrations.

⭐️Advantages

  • Modill is trained by 289 brilliant illustrations from different designers/illustrators. It can draw exaggerated-body characters and raster texture.

  • No strictly restrictions on style. The train data includes different styles, no-overfitting can generate more special outputs.

⭐️Recommendations of parameters

  • Sampler: DPM2 Karras, 20~40 steps.

  • CFG Scale: 7-9.

  • Resolutions: 512*512

  • Negatives: poorly lit, duplicated leg, no text, one shoe, multiple head, strange face , error head, missing hand, blur, stereopsis, sex, waterpoint

*** Add some Style Lora models might generate great arts. ***

⚡️Appendix for X/Y/Z script

DarkAlfa - Effortless high quality

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

Easy image quality that has a good context awareness!

This model was made with the intent of having great image quality, and good context awareness. It will respond to most types prompting styles, wether it be descriptions, lyrics, or simply tags. Masterpiece is not required, none of the images posted have 'masterpiece, best quality', or anything along that line. The image quality is good by default!

V1.1 Update summary

Much better context awareness, small loss of hand quality.

The continuation of a weird model!

Having used alfahentai for lot random art, it was only being held back by it's own confusion at times. This model is built upon the idea to get rid of that confusion and make a confident model. All the images i posted are only using Nerfgun3's Negative Hand embedding. The rest is pure txt2img prompt. No inpainting or other manipulation was done.

Big shoutout to Cryonicus, I want to believe his model was the missing part my model needed. Make sure to give his model a try too!

What this model is and isn't

Unfortunately, getting the art to improve to an incredible standard, it cost the model it's ability to make proper genitalia. Breasts still work though. Again, the model has been merged as much so that it retains it's general knowledge. It does NOT respond well booru specific tags/prompts. It might have recollections of some things you might expect in a lot of booru tagged models. For example Wariza doesn't function. Masterpiece has essentially been removed as tag and is generally not needed at all. For all the images I create, unless I stole someone's prompt, it will not have masterpiece/best quality ever. Honestly, i've tried comparisons and generally doesn't seem to add anything.

This model shines in it's ability to grasp concepts, context and general cohesion. I've tried various prompting styles on this model and they all seem to work. It works best with natural language and descriptions.

Model Usage

The model works best on a low CFG, i stick at 5. At 6 you already start getting the first symptoms of burn, at 7 it's really bad, and 8 and above simply seem unusable. The model has a lot of detail it can resolve, so it likes high stepcount, like it's predecessor. With UniPC and cfg 3 or 4 you test prompts with steps as low as 7. Take note, that sometimes your prompt will be interpreted differently if you change the aspect ratio. The unpruned image has a bit better image quality in my experience.

Sampler: UniPC

CFG: 5

Steps: 20-50

Clip skip: 1

Upscale: 4x Ultrasharp, denoise 0.5

Negative prompt used

negative_hand, (low quality:1.3), (worst quality:1.3), (lowres:1.3), (error:1.3), (fault:1.3), (undefined:1.3), (crude:1.3), jagged, spiky, ugly hands, extra arm, extra hand, split arm, missing finger, extra finger, three fingers, four fingers, six fingers, (disfigured:1.3), (unclear:1.3), (indistinct:1.3), merged fingers, (bad anatomy,:1.3) misplaced hand, misplaced foot,, cleavage, sex, nsfw, ecchi, slutty, leotard, (text:1.3), (signature:1.3), (title:1.3)

CityEdge FusionMix

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

日本語の説明は後半にあります。

This is a 2.5D merged model to realize 'fusion' in various aspects. Because of the complex merging process, I believe you will enjoy the characters and details that only this model can produce.

Specifically, the model has the following 'fusion' features.

  • This model is a 'fusion' merge model of both photorealistic and anime-like models, to create a 2.5D model.

  • Characters will be produced as the 'fusion' of Asian and Western styles.

  • The merging process is complex, and the merged models have unique 'fusion' details that are different from those of other merged models.

The merging process is generally as follows.

First, many photorealistic models are merged. The criteria for selecting models is if they can produce a photorealistic image when outputting a background without people. More than 15 models that meet this criterion are merged, including minor ones. Finally, only chilled remix and epiCRealism have a composition ratio of more than 10%. (A)

Next, a separate animated model is multi-block merged to create a clear, detailed, and descriptive animated model. This is basically the same as the one used in CityEdge StyleMix, and the main models used are: anything v5, Counterfeit v3, hassaku.(B)

Then, the model (B) is multi-block merged with the model (A) to create a 2.5D model. Finally, a thin layer of FaceBombMix, etc. is applied to ensure stability as a 2.5D model.

Both SFW and NSFW outputs are capable. High quality and unique images can be output in a short prompt. VAE is not needed, but you can try some.

List of my models

  • CityEdgeMix : Simple photo-realistic model based on Chilled family

  • CityEdge_ToonMix : Simple 2.5D anime-like model based on CityEdgeMix

  • CityEdge_2dToonMix : Pure 2D anime-like model merging only 2D models

  • CityEdge_StyleMix : Anime-like model with detail depiction by making use of block-merge

  • CityEdge_FusionMix : 2.5D model focusing on unique depiction through merging many models and block-merge.

さまざまな要素を融合（Fusion）させて作成した、2.5Dマージモデル。非常に複雑なマージプロセスを経ているため、このモデルでしか出せないキャラクターやディテールが楽しめると思います。

具体的には、以下のような特徴を持たせています。

  • 全体の描写は、フォトリアル系をベースにアニメ系を「融合」し2.5D化。

  • 人物描写は、アジア系をベースに欧米系を「融合」しエキゾチックに。

  • 複雑なモデルマージにより他のマージモデルとは異なる独自のディテールを表出。

マージプロセスは概ね以下のようになっています。

最初に、多数のフォトリアル系モデルをマージしています。モデルの選択基準は、人物なしの背景を出力した際にフォトリアルな画像を出せるかどうか。この基準に合致する15以上のモデルを、マイナーなものも含めマージしています。最終的に構成比が10%を超えているものはchilled remixとepiCRealismのみ。(A)

次に、別途アニメ系のモデルを階層マージし、クリアで詳細な描写のあるアニメモデルを作成しています。これはCityEdge StyleMixで利用したものと基本的に同じもので、使用している主なモデルは、Anything v5, Counterfeit v3, hassaku。(B)

そのうえで、(A)のモデルに(B)のモデルを階層マージし2.5D化。最後にFaceBombMix等を薄く重ねて2.5Dモデルとしての安定性を確保しています。

エロと非エロ、どちらにも対応。短いプロンプトで高品位かつ独自性のあるユニークな画像が出力できます。VAEは焼き込み済みですが別のものを使用してもいいと思います。

モデル一覧

  • CityEdgeMix : Chilled系をベースにしたシンプルなフォトリアル系マージモデル

  • CityEdge_ToonMix : CityEdgeMixを2.5D化したシンプルな2.5Dアニメモデル

  • CityEdge_2dToonMix : 2Dモデルだけをマージしたピュア2Dアニメモデル

  • CityEdge_StyleMix : 階層マージを駆使してディテール描写にこだわったアニメモデル

  • CityEdge_FusionMix : 多数のモデルのマージと階層マージによる独自の描写にこだわった2.5Dモデル

This is a global repository of the Dreambooth Checkpoints.

Some people asked me to upload the source Dreambooths from which I make the LyCORIS.

To not spam the site/profile with multiple models I decided to do it the same way I intended to handle the Game characters -> a single page where each model is just a separate version.

Upcoming: Billie Eilish, Eva Green, Olivia Wilde, Caity Lotz, Alissa White-Gluz

XenoEngine - An Art Style Mega Model

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

As always, the example images I've posted have NO postwork done to them beyond the facial fix (in some cases) and upscaling. The point is to show how well it works out of the box - if you take the time and create really good prompts and use good negative prompts (an example is at the end of this post) you can get even better results.

This is likely (assuming that there are no glaring issues or problems with this version) the final version of this model. If there are some discoveries I make which provide huge improvements to things, I might reconsider, but as of this writing, I'm very happy and satisfied, so it's time to move on and start training some new things and getting to work on my game engine.

(Updated for V4.5 FINAL VERSION: May 18,2023)
(Updated "Triggers" Sections: May, 15, 2023)

Intro

I wanted a model or workflow process that allowed me to quickly and easily churn out art for games and/or photo stories. I didn't want long complicated prompts to create a certain art style, but I also didn't want to be forced to use LoRa's and TI's for every character. Unfortunately, most of the models where I loved the art styles didn't do so well of loading characters (celebrities for mixing, fictional characters, etc.) and the ones that knew tons of famous characters and people tended not take to the art styles I was going for (at least not without complex prompts).

Triggers:

DIGITAL ART

WARLOCKANDBOOBS
Thickens the outlines a bit while keeping the skin a bit smoother. NOTE: At high weights, this can increase breast size and tend to push subjects toward medieval outfits.

CARTOON

MASTERPIECE

<SIZE> BREASTS - <SIZE> ASS - <SIZE> BELLY
Small - Medium - Large - Gigantic (See below for "Flat Chest" - "Small" does NOT necessarily make breasts smaller.) Just about anything with the word "breasts" in it is going to make them bigger. The more weight you use (and for Large and Gigantic calls) the higher the tendency to make it NSFW by default. (Call your outfits and use SFW in the prompt. NSFW in the negative prompt helps, too.

HYPERBREASTS

HYPERASS

FLAT CHEST
This does a pretty good job of getting the breasts smaller. The weight of this is fairly low in the model so just saying "flat chest" will give very subtle looks. Play with the weights a bit. Depending upon the subject, something like (flat_chest:1.5) give or take 0.1 either way will give them a nearly flat chest. Numbers between 1 and that top point will move along the scale between normal and flat. Usually.

DETAILED EYE
This will give the eyes more detail, but it also tends to drive the camera up to closeup shots - and doesn't really do all that much on anything further back than a cowboy shot. Expect usage of this to change the nature of the shot and either call your camera angle in the prompt or use EasyPose/Controlnet to force the character where you want them.

ADD DETAIL
Based upon the Detail Tweaker LoRa - I baked in just a smidge of this (so there's no real reason or need to use it again with this model). Just put add_detail into the prompt with a weight (higher or lower as desired) to tweak the detail levels.

Fun Triggers

These are not really things I purposely put into the model, but that produce fun and/or interesting results. These triggers may very well work with other models you use, too.

Feminization: Something like "Chuck Norris, feminization," along with whatever else you want in a prompt will create something that would be maybe what Chuck Norris would look like as a woman.

Sanpaku: shrinks the iris of the eye a bit making more of the eye whites show and giving them a bit more detailed look. Increase the weight to make the irises even smaller (and more whites showing).

See "Version Details" to the right for minor revision update notes. This post will be updated with major notes, triggers, and other long-term items.

V4 Update Notes

Rebuilt from the ground up... got rid of some garbage (and pruned it down to half its original size) tweaked some weights that were bothering me, and generally got things cleaned up. I'm not quite happy with the style consistency, yet - but this is a good clean start on things.

NOTE: The trigger words listed are just the ones that were specifically added on top of the SD Base Model - and really only the ones I've found useful to make good tweaks and adjustments. This model is great at knowing art styles, people, and concepts that you might love (and/or hate) from the base model.

I also forgot one ingredient when adding hyperfusion - so it tends to go porny/nude when you start playing with breasts. I won't have time to update/fix until this weekend so... expect to have to do some work to add clothes if you're playing with breast sizes. Sorry about that.

V3.X Update Notes

Keywords "Masterpiece" and "add_detail" will enhance (or back down if negative levels are used).

This also responds to the Hyperfusion triggers (see version 3.2 notes) as well as all the custom art styles from Babes. (Plus many many more - but the Babes trained styles are ones likely not to be found in many other models).

A bonus (from Hyperfusion) is that it also lets you accomplish making breasts smaller - something very difficult to do on most models without bringing in a lot of extra help. With this "flat_chest:1.4" (or thereabouts) will do a nice job of shrinking things down in most cases. You can also use all the triggers from hyperfusion to make the breasts, butt, and belly do all sorts of things - and putting in weights there brings varied results too.

NOTE: At low levels, most of those calls don't go crazy by sexing everyone up. The higher your weights, the more likely that is to happen, so you may need to declare SFWs and even call a specific outfit in some cases. (I had to do that in the big bust sample image).

All previous triggers and keywords will still work, too.


Some notes on the model:

  • It "mostly" defaults to SFW out of the box. i.e. If you just type in a person's name or character description with no clothes - it'll tend to put them in clothes - or at least a swimsuit. That said... with proper prompting, does nudes and porny stuff just fine, too.

  • I didn't care so much about making sure resulting characters look "exactly" like the person you're calling out so much as wanting to make sure that if I called out that name/person again - they'd be consistent in the way they look from image to image. So, in other words, it's not so much about "accuracy" as it is about "consistency" - and that seems to come through. (This works well for my needs to create stories and whatnot)

Good Negative Prompt for this Model
canvas frame, 3d, ((disfigured)), ((bad art)), ((deformed)),((extra limbs)),((b&w)), blurry, (((duplicate))), ((morbid)), ((mutilated)), [out of frame], extra fingers, mutated hands, ((poorly drawn hands)), ((poorly drawn face)), (((mutation))), (((deformed))), ((ugly)), blurry, ((bad anatomy)), (((bad proportions))), ((extra limbs)), cloned face, (((disfigured))), out of frame, ugly, extra limbs, (bad anatomy), gross proportions, (malformed limbs), ((missing arms)), ((missing legs)), (((extra arms))), (((extra legs))), mutated hands, (fused fingers), (too many fingers), (((long neck))), ugly, tiling, poorly drawn hands, poorly drawn feet, poorly drawn face, out of frame, mutation, mutated, extra limbs, extra legs, extra arms, disfigured, deformed, cross-eye, body out of frame, blurry, bad art, bad anatomy, Scribbles, Low quality, Low rated, Mediocre, 3D rendering, Screenshot, Software, UI, watermark, signature, distorted pupils, distorted eyes, (distorted face), Unnatural anatomy, strange anatomy, things on face, ((tattoo)), ((tattoos)),

Updated to v2.1 Change Log

  • Improved realism quality in general, it moves away from 2.5D feel from the previous version while maintaining fantasy capabilities.

  • Improved vanilla NSFW prompts

  • Improved SDE sampler quality - no more weirdly lit faces when using SDE sampler in ver. 1 especially in dark scene (observed faster baking time, or maybe its me getting more patient)

  • Lower problems with Dynamic CFG threshold when using my lycoris in this version

  • hands still sometimes messed up at higher CFG - observed with multiple test scene with controlled seed with 3 comparison model vs. my model. with : 1. no neg-Ti, 2. single neg-Ti, or 3. combined neg-Ti. (Ti in this case doesn't really do shit, it did its job reducing the problems - so its mostly problem with my model, i suspect maybe its because i merged with a SD21 model with hentai model, but who knows.)

  • the VAE 84000 should be already baked in

  • Do note that your results may vary than my testing. just pray to the god of Ai often.

How do I come Up with this Mix?

Well, I'm not an Ai engineer, so i dont really understand fully the inner workings of a base model, more than what Stable-Diffusion has put in their github page. I'm basically a designer that has high enthusiast towards Image generative Ai. So, this mix is done through trial and errors - basically I have a set of checklists that is mostly compiled after using SD since i joined CivitAi, the mix should be able to do all these checklists that i put for testing before i further improve or add another mix in.

What if the resulting mix fails one or more checklists? i rolled back to previous mix and tries to change mix values, or even change base model for mixing, thats why its going back and forth processes until I find one that is suitable for most use cases for me personally. There are 1 iterations somewhere in this model where i tried to combine the base model SD1.5 with a SD2.1 models, I dont know if this can cause problems in the future but so far, everything is fine to me.

Did you prune the model? - I'm not sure, definitely im not using .py script to prune the model, but there are pruned model used as a base mix. chilloutmix pruned is one of them (very-very early iterations).

Why do you put so many embeddings or loras to create the sample images? - these are a long processes since the beginning when i used SD, for embeddings, at first i just copied people's post negative prompt to learn, but as i understand more, i made my own, and that stabilizes over time, as you encounters a problem, you add negative prompts to counter that problem until it dissapears, and so on - finally it came to the point where you see in the sample image. these are not random as it may seem, and it is the result of controlled testing. (while maybe a very crude and a dumb-dumb way of brute force manual testing)

as for lora: all the loras used in the sample images are my lora. it is meant to show how the model interact with my lora, which is the point of the mix in the first place, only embeddings i use are other people's work, and credits due to all of them and you can find them in the resources section below.

Why make this Mix?

Short answer is to better integrate with my own lora.

I really love fantasticmix & henmix model, both are very great in creating the style i really like, and especially realism for henmix, be sure to check their models as well. I've been using their model alot and i love it, but i encountered these:

  1. Since I'm starting doing my own lycoris, problems starts to arise like overbaking, distorted hands, multiple limbs, even with negative prompts and negative Ti already in place. especially with NSFW prompt, important research anatomies of human bodies gets really bad.

  2. Low Sizes! another reason is that Im quickly filling up my disk drive, with so much models that i ended up not using or having to test, moreover 8GB models is a turn off for me, so I decided to just really make one that suits my taste & style and mix nicely with my own locon.

  3. I like to have versatility in my model, i often switch between models because i want to go for conceptual art with realistic subject, other time i want to go for complete realism, this model tries to achieve that in a single model, while maybe its not perfect.

  4. I like concise prompt, and not having to put too many enhancer prompts such as: photorealistic:1.4, ultra-hires, hi-res, hyperrealistic, masterpiece, 4k, 8k, rawphoto, cinematic lighting, absurdres , etc, etc, i just want to write realistic, and i want it to get there, so i can focus more on prompting the subject / environment / action instead of focusing too much on that part.

  5. I use alot of 2:3 ratio instead of 3:2, so i need the model that is kind of optimized for this ratio.

  6. If you ever watch kimi no nawa or suzune, it kinds of describe the anime style that i like. a very detailed environment, with a crisp outline. the anime version of this model achieved that with NSFW capabilities.

  7. All in all basically i just want less headache and focus on creating beautiful stuff.

To prompt this mix

  1. Style —> realistic , realistic details, detailed for realism / anime for anime / masterpiece , best illustration for conceptual art.

  2. Subject —> describe your subject can be anything. 1girl, solo, cute, beautiful, slender, etc. if you use my character lora this should be where you put trigger words of the character

  3. Attire —> describe the outfit of your subject. If you use my attire lora this is where you should put trigger words

  4. Background / Context —> describe the context or the scene

  5. Textual Inversion & LoRa brackets

  6. You can follow your own prompting method, this guide only serves as a convention when you are having trouble producing similar results with my lora.

How to maximize this mix?

Sampler & Embeddings

Using 2M Karras is good enough most of the time to create good images with less baking time, you can further improve the detail with SDE Karras, in version 1, this messes up the face lighting quite often (such as lit face even though the context is dark), in version 2 this is fixed for most cases (at least in my test).


Using negative embeddings is a must to create sample image quality. I don't really care the inner workings of my model and i don't want to find out further, all i care is that the model can produce what i want at the quality i desire, and can tackle most scenarios that i need.

CFG Scale

  • Lower CFG Scale means AI gets more creative and less overbaking problems. the down side is that the results tends to get a plasticky view.

  • Higher CFG Scale means results get more realistic, and very accurate with training sets and more prone to overbaking problems.

  • Dynamic CFG Threshold ( only use when necessary ) -- using this method allows you to bump up quality and achieve photorealistic easily, so you basically get both Lower CFG & Higher CFG Advantage and eliminate both problems, the downside is that sometimes it doesn't work with specific lycoris for some reasons. The settings that i most often use: Mimic CFG 5-10 , Clamp 99.5 Percentile, 2nd weight slider = 0 - Cosine Up, third weight slider = 15 Half Cosine Down (sorry i kinda forgot the name)

Repeats & Hi Res Fix

  • Higher repeats means your Ai has more time to generate the image, resulting in better result. generally 50 is enough, with 1/2 value for high res fix repeat.

  • I use 512 x 768, with ERSGAN_4x+ at 2x upscale. which then i will send to extras with upscaler to further 2x again with ERSGAN_4x or 4xUltraSharp (for anime). the settings i find superior are : GPFGAN @0.25, Codeformer @0.3 & weight 0.15

Utilizing ADetailer & DDetailer

  • I use ADetailer to auto fix hands & enhance detail of the body. But sometimes this can go against you especially on anime version.

  • I use DDetailer to fix face, but if you find it hard to install DDetailer, it may be better to use ADetailer second pass to fix face instead of body. it yields similar results as DDetailer.

The rule of thumb is that there are no constant equation, you need to find one your own that suits what you are aiming, and sometimes you change these value on the fly depending on your goal. its better to know what these parameters do to your results rather than copying values from people's post.

--

As an afterwords, i hope you enjoy using this model, a like or a review definitely helps, or if you find it distasteful, you don't have to use it. there are many models out there that produces similar or superior results.

Pruning Info

The model is pruned with the following settings using this repo from 4GB to 2GB at virtually no difference in the generations.

python prune.py --fp16 --ema --no-depth delicate_v10.ckpt delicate-v1-0-full-ema-pruned.ckpt

Simply download the script prune.py, create a new conda environment (conda create -n prune), then activate it with conda activate prune. Run pip install numpy safetensors torch!=1.13.0. Then run the command above and replace the first checkpoint name with your non-pruned one and the second checkpoint name with whatever you want your pruned model to be called. Don't use safetensors as the extension (use ckpt instead), otherwise it may fail during inference. You can convert pickle ckpt to safetensor in the Checkpoint Merging tab of Automatic1111.

Vodka by FollowFox.AI

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

Overview

TLDR: We are releasing Vodka_V2 by FollowFox.AI, a general-purpose model fine-tuned on an updated dataset - now from Midjourney V5.1. And as usual, in this post, we will share all the details how we got there. What you should expect from the mode:

  • We used an objectively better dataset - 2.5x larger, which was cleaned better.

  • The resulting model is quite similar to V1 but marginally better. It’s a step up but not a breakthrough-type improvement.

  • In the current state, we can generate some cool images with some effort

  • The model is still far from effortlessly and consistently generating MidJourney or even top SD models level output


You can read all the details about the model training process on followfox.ai (link to the post), as we can embrace the open-source nature of this community. You can recreate the process, see exactly how we got here, and provide feedback and suggestions on individual aspects of the protocol.

Parameters and Workflow that Works Well for Vodka V2

There is a lot more to test here, but we will share a few observations:

  • Compared to V1, you can try a wider range of CFG values; anything from 3 to 7.5 can generate good output

  • Booru tag-only prompts do not work well since we didn’t tag the dataset

  • Human sentence-type description followed by adjectives and “magic words” works quite well

  • Almost all samplers seem to generate interesting results.

  • SD upscale workflow (outlined below) with tile ControlNet enhances the image quality of this model

  • Using EasyNegative TI (link) is recommended. “blurry” in negative prompts also helps.

Upscale Workflow to Try in Automatic1111

After generating the initial image you like in the txt2img tab (we recommend doing a grid of different samplers and CFG values for each prompt to find the promising ones), send it to img2img.

  • Use the same prompt and sampler as in the original generation

  • Set sample steps high; in our case, we used 150 for most of the images

  • Set width and height to 2x the original. So 512x512 should have 1024x1024

  • Set the denoising strength to something low; we used 0.2 to 0.25.

  • For the CFG value, we used the (original - 0.5) formula. So if the original image was generated at 7.0, we would set it to 6.5.

  • ControlNet settings: enable it; for preprocessor select “tile_resample,” and for model ‘control_v11f1e_sd15_tile’. You can also switch to the “ControlNet is more important” option. No need to adjust any other settings.

  • Make sure to have the “Ultimate SD upscale” extension installed. Select it from the Script dropdown, select the 4x-UltraSharp upscaler, and set tile width and height to 640x640.

  • Press generate, wait a bit, and you should have a decent output. You can repeat the process to go even higher resolution.

Conclusions and Next Steps

We believe the model development is going in the right direction, and we will continue releasing the new versions. And, of course, we will document and release every step of that journey.

For the V3 release, we already have a working hypothesis of where the blurriness and lack of details in some of the generations might be coming from, and we will try to deal with that.

MothMix

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

Increasingly complex mix I made for use in my own works. Version 1.3 is a bit more stylized, and may not be for everyone, but I like it, and it can still give the high level of detail I appreciate from the model so far. The recipe details are published below, and the result is a model that is still stylized, but intricately detailed and able to represent cultures from around the world. I've noticed in doing characters that have darker skin, I don't have to fight stable diffusion anywhere near as much as I used to. It's very versatile and finally feels like its more then the sum of its parts. I use it for concept art, and I feel it fills that role perfectly. Also yes, the model can do NSFW.

Source Models:
MeinaMixV9
Aurora
NeverEnding Dream
GeminiX_Mix
Utopia

Recipe info:
1.0: 55% MeinaMixV9 : 45% Aurora

1.1: MothMix v1.0 + 0.3 NeverEnding Dream

1.2 (unpublished): MothMix v1.1 + 0.15 GeminiX_Mix

1.21: MothMix v1.2 + 0.15 MeinaMixV9

1.3: MothMix v1.21 + 0.15 Utopia

In the interest of honesty I will disclose that many of these pictures here have been cherry picked, hand-edited and re-generated. That's because the majority are working pieces of concept art for a story I'm working on. I don't want to give the impression that this model can't give good first-generation images - it can - but when using it you should just kind of expect to have to hi-res fix and/or inpaint at least once. None of the pictures posted here use a Lora for style, but as part of the typical prompt I use they do use EasyNegative and BadHandV4 at usually reduced weights (0.6 and 0.4 respectively). The ones that do use Lora are only for character specific features (Moth Girls, Obsidian Skin, Black Sclera, etc.). If you find you're still having issues with characters with dark skin, look into DuskFallCrew's Dark Fantasy Lora, its made for creating dark skinned characters in anime models. All images were post-process upscaled with 4x_NMKD-Superscale-SP_178000_G to give a painted look. If you're wondering why all my pictures have extremely high CFG scales, its because I use Dynamic Thresholding. If you're doing anything where you want a very specific result based on prompts alone, I highly recommend it. After testing, high CFG + DT didn't show much improvement over low CFG (~7), so YMMV. The parameters I use for all images are:
Mimic CFG Scale - 7 (rarely 3)
Mimic/CFG Scale Scheduler - Half Cosine Up
Min. Value of Mimic/CFG Scale Scheduler - 3

Below are recommended gen info based on the stuff I typically use, combined with legal stuff inherited from its composite models, who thankfully use the same license parameters. This mix uses CreativeML OpenRAIL-M as the two previous models do, and since Meina disallows the use of the model on generation services or paid services without her consent, this model is similarly banned for use in similar contexts.

Recommendations:

Enable Quantization in K samplers.

Hires.fix in some form is needed for high quality images. You can either use the t2i hires fix, which I'd recommend running at 1.5-2x scale at 0.3 denoising for 15 steps. I do this manually by running the best finished images through img2img

Recommended parameters:
Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras: 25-35 steps.
CFG Scale: 7+. See note on Dynamic Thresholding above.
Resolutions:
-Default: 512x512 txt2img -> 1024x1024 img2img, 0.3-0.65 Denoising
-512x768, 512x1024 for Portrait
-768x432, 1024x576 for Landscape (16:9)
Hires.fix: 4x_NMKD-Superscale-SP_178000_G or 4x_fatal_Anime_500000_G, with 15 steps at ~0.3 denoising.
Clip Skip: 1 or 2.
Negatives: ' (worst quality:2, low quality:2), (zombie, sketch, interlocked fingers, comic), '

Prohibition is a high quality model trained on Public Domain, CC0 licensed Life Magazine and Country Gentleman magazine cover illustrations between 1914 and 1937, but with a primary focus on illustrations produced between 1920 and 1933 during the Prohibition era.

Example prompt (keyword triggers are in bold):

sd-prohib a female bartender in a white shirt, vest and tie making a cocktail during prohibition, medium brushstrokes, painterly, dynamic, family life, idealism, pictorial, country gentleman, 1920, cover art, illustration

Recommended Negative prompt keywords: logo, wordmark, signature, title, text, words, magazine cover

Subtle variations can be produced by reusing the same seed and changing the year:[1914|1920|1924|1925|1928|1930|1933|1934|1937]

switching between [broad brushstrokes|medium brushstrokes|fine brushstrokes]

switching between [country gentleman|life magazine]

and switching between [family life|adventure|romance]

Sharing this model with the community. As it closely resembles Lexica Art V2 or Lexica Aperture v2, this product is an excellent choice.

It's absolutely amazing how we're able to create incredibly realistic faces with only a few simple steps.

Enhance your writing prompt by adding the estilovintedois prefix, as it guarantees a consistent writing style.

"While you're welcome to use this model, please keep in mind that any potential damages or mishaps resulting from its use are not our responsibility..."

"This model was trained on a large amount of high quality images with simple prompts to generate beautiful images without a lot of prompt engineering."

"It should also be very dreamboothable, being able to generate high fidelity faces with a little amount of steps."

This model is based on vintedois_diffusion. Credit to the original developers.
Vintedois (22h) Diffusion model trained by Predogl and piEsposito with open weights, configs and prompts (as it should be).
